8%2C363&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-21560 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1992-10-02b.jpg?resize=758%2C362&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"362\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1992-10-02b.jpg?w=2432&amp;ssl=1 2432w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1992-10-02b.jpg?resize=300%2C143&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1992-10-02b.jpg?resize=1024%2C490&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1992-10-02b.jpg?resize=768%2C367&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1992-10-02b.jpg?resize=1536%2C735&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1992-10-02b.jpg?resize=2048%2C979&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1992-10-02b.jpg?w=2274&amp;ssl=1 2274w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>1996:\u00a0</strong>Bruce plays a solo acoustic show at the Riverside Theater in Milwaukee, 21 years to the day of the infamous Bomb Scare Show (see above). Following the show, Bruce zips over to the Bradley Center, where he joins Melissa Etheridge on stage for a duet on &#8220;Pink Cadillac.&#8221;</p>\n<div id=\"v-1La8VWX2-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='426' src='https://videopress.com/embed/1La8VWX2?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" load